                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d241">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.3212/61: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-10-30T15:00:00-03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 30, 1920—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>105. Have communicated substance of Department’s October 29, 7 p.m., containing
                    statement given to press, to Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs who has
                    received telegram from Alencar<note n="34" xml:id="d241fn34">Augusto Cochrane de
                        Alencar, Brazilian Ambassador at Washington.</note> in the same sense.
                    Minister has declined for the present to receive officially Torre Díaz who
                    arrived on October 26th as Mexican Minister to Brazil, alleging as a reason that
                    his <hi rend="italic">agrément</hi> has not been granted. May however meet him
                    unofficially next week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
